<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.48B/10: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Woods</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Iwaki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-04"><hi rend="italic">September 4,
                                    1923</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 10:55 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Communications have just been opened up with Yokohama. The situation
                            there is exceedingly serious and some Americans are reported to have
                            lost their lives. The casualties in Tokio are estimated at 10,000. I
                            believe all Americans in Tokio are safe. The food situation is acute.
                            Send supply from Philippines at once as already requested. The
                            fire-proof vault of the Embassy was not fire-proof and all Embassy
                            records are burned.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Woods</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>